### Implementation 1: Basic Kalman Filter Prediction

```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = P @ S.T @ np.linalg.inv(S)
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

