### Implementation 1: Matrix Multiplication with Identity Update
```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.eye(x.shape[0])
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

### Implementation 2: Adaptive Kalman Filter with Time-Varying Transition
```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.linalg.inv(P @ F.T + S @ F) @ (P @ y)
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

### Implementation 3: Simple Linear Transformation
```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.ones_like(P)
    x = xp + K * y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

### Implementation 4: Probabilistic Update with Gaussian Mixture
```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.diag(np.exp(-np.sum(y**2, axis=1)/2))
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

