### Implementation 7: Robust Kalman Filter with Huber Loss
```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    rho = 1 + 0.1 * np.mean(np.abs(y))
    inv_rho = 1 / rho
    K = np.linalg.inv(P @ F.T + inv_rho * S @ F) @ (P @ y)
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

### Implementation 8: Polynomial Regression Update
```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    xp = F @ x
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.polyval(np.polyfit(y.flatten(), x.flatten(), 2)) * np.eye(x.shape[0])
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

