    K = np.eye(x.shape[0])
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

### Implementation 8: Quadratic Transformation with Threshold

```python
def predict(x, F, P, Q, z, R):
    threshold = 0.5
    xp = (F @ x) ** 2 * (F @ x > threshold)
    y = z - xp
    S = Q + R
    K = np.eye(x.shape[0])
    x = xp + K @ y
    return xp, P, y, S, K, x
```

